sequenceDiagram
    actor Admin
    participant SPA as DDoS Protection tab
    participant API as FastAPI /ddos (admin)
    participant DB as PostgreSQL
    participant WK as BlockedPortReconciler
    participant DP as dpstat set-blocked-ports
    participant MAP as udp_blocked_port_bitmap
    participant HOT as XDP BLK stage

    Admin->>SPA: Add UDP port 9999 (+ note)
    SPA->>API: POST /ddos/amplification/ports
    API->>DB: INSERT blocked_udp_port(9999)
    API->>DB: record_event ddos.amp_port.added
    API-->>SPA: 201 (toast: applying to data-plane)

    Note over WK: background loop, tick ~1s
    WK->>DB: SELECT desired port set
    WK->>WK: desired != asserted_ports ?
    WK->>DP: exec set-blocked-ports 9999 ...
    DP->>MAP: slot 0 inner: word[9999>>6] |= 1<<(9999&63)
    DP->>MAP: slot 1 inner: same (carry-forward-safe)
    DP-->>WK: exit 0
    WK->>WK: asserted_ports = desired

    Note over MAP,HOT: hot path reads pinned active slot (no code change)
    HOT->>MAP: UDP source port 9999 lookup
    HOT-->>HOT: bit set -> udp_amplification_drop (idx 7)

    Note over MAP: later, an unrelated service/feed apply runs
    DP-->>MAP: xdpgw-apply carry_forward: pointer-install active inner<br/>into inactive slot (content preserved, never cleared)
    Note over HOT: 9999 still blocked after the flip (AMP-11)

    alt dpstat write fails (gateway not loaded / timeout)
        WK->>WK: keep last-good asserted, log, retry next tick
        Note over MAP: previously blocked ports stay blocked (fail-safe, AMP-10)
    end
